        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 12:38PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1238 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
northeast of Poteau, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Cameron...                        Poteau...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
